      "content": "the problem is everything is digital. i go outside and it's just more people looking at their phones, looking past me like i'm not even there. it's like my entire existence is just a series of notifications and Slack messages. if the notifications just stopped... if i just stopped responding... it doesn't feel like anyone would even notice the gap. i feel totally invisible.",
